u-571 is a 2000 french-american war film directed by jonathan mostow and starring matthew mcconaughey , bill paxton , harvey keitel , thomas kretschmann , jon bon jovi , jack &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , will estes and tom &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . in the film , a world war ii german submarine is boarded in 1942 by disguised united states navy &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; seeking to capture her enigma cipher machine . the film was financially successful and generally well-received by critics , and won an academy award for sound editing . the fictitious plot attracted substantial criticism ; in reality , it was british personnel from hms bulldog who first captured a naval enigma machine ( from &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; in the north atlantic in may 1941 ) , months before the united states had even entered the war . the anger over the inaccuracies even reached the british parliament , where prime minister tony blair stated that the film was an " &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; " to british sailors . the film was also criticized for portraying german u-boat crews in a negative light .